 {"id": "franken_networkx-bulkgen", "title": "REVIEW: [MEDIUM] 11 algorithm functions returned list instead of generator", "description": "nx contract: find_cliques, find_cliques_recursive, enumerate_all_cliques, all_simple_paths, all_shortest_paths, bfs_edges, dfs_edges, bfs_layers, isolates, minimum_spanning_edges, maximum_spanning_edges all return generators. fnx returned materialised lists. User code calling next(iter) TypeErrored. Wrapped each at module init to return an iterator. Updated 10 existing tests that encoded the list contract.", "status": "closed", "priority": 3, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T12:20:29.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T12:20:29.000000000Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T12:20:29.000000000Z", "close_reason": "Bulk-promote via iter() wrapper at module init", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-adjiter", "title": "REVIEW: [MEDIUM] Graph.adjacency returned list instead of iterator", "description": "nx.Graph.adjacency() returns a dict_itemiterator (iter-able). fnx returned a materialised list so next(G.adjacency()) TypeErrored. Changed both _simple_graph_adjacency and _multigraph_adjacency to yield lazily so the contract matches.", "status": "closed", "priority": 3, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T12:31:09.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T12:31:09.000000000Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T12:31:09.000000000Z", "close_reason": "Return generator instead of list", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-kedgegen", "title": "REVIEW: [MEDIUM] k_edge_components returned list instead of generator", "description": "nx.k_edge_components returns a generator. fnx returned a list. User code calling next(k_edge_components(G, k=2)) TypeErrored. Wrapped in iter() and split internal-use _k_edge_components_list helper for k_edge_subgraphs which iterates internally. Updated 2 existing tests that used len() on the return.", "status": "closed", "priority": 3, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T12:31:09.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T12:31:09.000000000Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T12:31:09.000000000Z", "close_reason": "iter() wrapper + helper", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
+{"id": "franken_networkx-viewitems", "title": "REVIEW: [LOW] AdjacencyView.items/values returned one-shot generators instead of re-iterable Views", "description": "nx.EdgeView.items returns an ItemsView that can be iterated multiple times. fnx returned a one-shot generator \u2014 second iteration yielded empty. Wrapped in ItemsView/ValuesView subclasses so list(ev.items()) works twice. Same fix for AdjacencyView/MultiAdjacencyView + _DiGraphEdgeView via the shared _adjacency_view_items/values helpers.", "status": "closed", "priority": 4, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T12:32:54.000000000Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T12:32:54.000000000Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-24T12:32:54.000000000Z", "close_reason": "ItemsView/ValuesView wrappers", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
